The paper presents an AI agent for managing micro-tasks on crowdsourcing marketplaces, which involves balancing conflicting objectives of quality, cost, and time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the development of the AI agent, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) for the focus on managing micro-tasks on crowdsourcing marketplaces, Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) for the optimization of cost-quality-time tradeoffs, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) for the multi-agent formulation, and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the use of crowdsourcing marketplaces.
